label("$\frac{2}{3} DE$", (F + E)/2, NE);
label("$\frac{3}{7} BC$", (B + T)/2, S);
label("$\frac{4}{7} BC$", (C + T)/2, S);
[/asy]

Since $DF = \frac{1}{3} DE$ and $FE = \frac{2}{3} DE,$ $DE = DF + FE = \frac{3}{3} DE = DE.$  Also, $BT = \frac{3}{7} BC$ and $CT = \frac{4}{7} BC,$ so $BC = BT + CT = \frac{7}{7} BC = BC.$  Hence,
\[\frac{AF}{AT} = \frac{DF}{BT} = \frac{\frac{1}{3} DE}{\frac{3}{7} BC} = \frac{7 DE}{9 BC} = \frac{7}{9} \cdot \frac{DE}{BC}.\]Since $DE$ and $BC$ are corresponding sides of similar triangles $DEF$ and $BTC,$ $\frac{DE}{BC} = \frac{DF}{BT} = \frac{1}{3},$ so
\[\frac{AF}{AT} = \frac{7}{9} \cdot \frac{1}{3} = \boxed{\frac{7}{27}}.\]

